{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Corinthians 6 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:1",
      "text": "And we helping do exhort you that you receive not the grace of God in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:2",
      "text": "For he saith: In an accepted time have I heard thee and in the day of salvation have I helped thee. Behold, now is the acceptable time: behold, now is the day of salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:3",
      "text": "Giving no offence to any man, that our ministry be not blamed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:4",
      "text": "But in all things let us exhibit ourselves as the ministers of God, in much patience, in tribulation, in necessities, in distresses,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:5",
      "text": "In stripes, in prisons, in seditions, in labours, in watchings, in fastings,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:6",
      "text": "In chastity, in knowledge, in longsuffering, in sweetness, in the Holy Ghost, in charity unfeigned,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:7",
      "text": "In the word of truth, in the power of God: by the armour of justice on the right hand and on the left:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:8",
      "text": "By honour and dishonour: by evil report and good report: as deceivers and yet true: as unknown and yet known:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:9",
      "text": "As dying and behold we live: as chastised and not killed:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:10",
      "text": "As sorrowful, yet always rejoicing: as needy, yet enriching many: as having nothing and possessing all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:11",
      "text": "Our mouth is open to you, O ye Corinthians: our heart is enlarged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:12",
      "text": "You are not straitened in us: but in your own bowels you are straitened.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:13",
      "text": "But having the same recompense (I speak as to my children): be you also enlarged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:14",
      "text": "Bear not the yoke with unbelievers. For what participation hath justice with injustice? Or what fellowship hath light with darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:15",
      "text": "And what concord hath Christ with Belial? Or what part hath the faithful with the unbeliever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:16",
      "text": "And what agreement hath the temple of God with idols? For you are the temple of the living God: as God saith: I will dwell in them and walk among them. And I will be their God: and they shall be my people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:17",
      "text": "Wherefore: Go out from among them and be ye separate, saith the Lord, and touch not the unclean thing:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-corinthians.6.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:18",
      "text": "And I will receive you. And will be a Father to you: and you shall be my sons and daughters, saith the Lord Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
